bio: Ella thinks climbing is fun, but it is difficult with only flippers and so her favorite pastime is actually blinking and rolling around on snow.
A wonderful wit while whispers waft wonders wandering *butthole* waters with wishes wrot whisked wimples wrinkling wrath.

Since the age of 7, Max has been working on building the thickest pelt possible, such that no matter what high she falls from in slow motion, she will never be injured. Current thickness is measured at 7.25 centimetres.

Austin is currently a zero looking to become a hero. He is studying under the legendary Ellen Currin in order to harness her infamous rock crushing abilities and the slothly Kerry Scott in hopes to become the first climber to take 2 hours to complete a 50 foot 5.10.

Ellen is ranked as the worlds greatest female climber. Now that she has crushed every single rock on planet earth, she is moving on to bigger and better things: She will be joining Mars One and will be brining rock climbing to the first human settlement on mars! Watch out galaxy, here she comes.

Abigail has been climbing since she was three years old, which also happens to be the year her hands stopped growing. She has the worlds tiniest hands. Literally. They are basically nubs on her arms. While crimps are a breeze for this tiny-handed lady, jugs are absolutely unmanagable unless she jams her arm all the way in up to her elbow! It has never stopped her from climbing, and she says it never will.

Alexander loves climbing, but the tiny siamese twin that he keeps hidden under his shirt is scared of heights. (Un)fortunately, Alexander doesnt care much about his siamese twin, so he has no problem sending 6 pitches.

Adam Bock is the world's first (and only) upside-down climber. For the past ten years, Adam exclusively walks on his hands, and he maintains his inverted posture while climbing. No, he does not wear special shoes. Yes, he does have hook-like toes.
If Cubler had to choose a natural science, he’d have to go with physics. Not so big into the study of life and living organisms, but has recently becoming interested in epigenetics.

Brad has actually never climbed. He walked into the climbing gym one day because he was looking for his physics classroom, but then he never left. Ever. Now he sleeps in the climbing gym, because the bouldering pads are more comfortable than the camping pad that he used to use as a bed.
